Package com.parse

Class ParseCloud

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.parse.ParseCloud
  • public final class ParseCloud
extends java.lang.Object
    The ParseCloud class defines provides methods for interacting with Parse Cloud Functions. A Cloud Function can be called with callFunctionInBackground(String, Map, FunctionCallback) using a FunctionCallback. For example, this sample code calls the "validateGame" Cloud Function and calls processResponse if the call succeeded and handleError if it failed. 

     ParseCloud.callFunctionInBackground("validateGame", parameters, new FunctionCallback
